-- Commerzbank shares up on Citigroup bid talk: traders
-- 
-- Tue Jun 5, 2007 10:12am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/05/us-commerzbank-bid-idUSL0529469820070605

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Commerzbank ( CBKG.DE ), which has been persistently cited as a possible takeover target, jumped 2.2 percent to 37.8 euros, its highest in nearly seven years on market talk Citigroup ( C.N ) was likely to bid about 45 euros a share for the bank. 

 By 0910 GMT 3.5 million shares were traded in Commerzbank, which compares with an average daily volume of about 4.96 million over the past 30 days. Commerzbank declined comment on the market rumor. Its shares were the top gainers in the DAX 30 share index  .GDAXI , which was up 0.1 percent. Sue Harnett, Citigroup's head of German operations told Reuters in late March that Citigroup was on the lookout for acquisitions in Germany and could swoop on a big bank.